1
00:00:10,125 --> 00:00:11,291
I'm his daughter.

2
00:00:11,375 --> 00:00:13,166
Yes… I can't make it today,

3
00:00:13,250 --> 00:00:15,541
but his caregiver will take him there.

4
00:00:15,625 --> 00:00:17,916
Could you please wait a bit longer for us?

5
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:23,250
Of course,
I know doctors need to rest too.

6
00:00:23,333 --> 00:00:24,416
I'm really sorry.

7
00:00:25,833 --> 00:00:27,333
Sorry, just a second.

8
00:00:28,291 --> 00:00:30,208
Hey, sorry. His caregiver is calling.

9
00:00:30,291 --> 00:00:32,416
I'll call you right back. Thank you.

10
00:00:33,625 --> 00:00:35,458
Yani, where are you?

11
00:00:36,750 --> 00:00:37,916
Why are you in Zhongli?

12
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,125
Didn't I tell you last week…

13
00:00:46,750 --> 00:00:47,958
Yani, listen.

14
00:00:48,875 --> 00:00:51,166
It's okay.
I'll take him to the hospital now.

15
00:00:51,250 --> 00:00:53,833
Once you're in Taipei,
go straight to the hospital, okay?

16
00:00:53,916 --> 00:00:55,583
Yes, okay. Bye-bye.

17
00:00:59,208 --> 00:01:01,458
Can't she go to the hospital alone?

18
00:01:01,541 --> 00:01:03,500
We're going to the hospital now.

19
00:01:07,833 --> 00:01:09,166
Who's "we"?

20
00:01:13,791 --> 00:01:15,833
You look so tired.

21
00:01:17,125 --> 00:01:18,291
I'm fine.

22
00:01:18,375 --> 00:01:19,666
I mean it, yeah.

23
00:01:25,125 --> 00:01:27,000
You need someone to look after you.

24
00:01:31,916 --> 00:01:34,458
I'm grown up now.
I can take care of myself.

25
00:01:39,333 --> 00:01:42,916
However grown up you are,
you should be looked after.

26
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:56,916
Thank you.

27
00:02:27,666 --> 00:02:32,333
IF YOU FORGET
I WILL REMEMBER IT ALL FOR YOU

28
00:02:35,458 --> 00:02:37,291
Nini, I'm sorry.

29
00:02:37,375 --> 00:02:38,208
He's inside.

30
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,500
Cheng Le-le.

31
00:02:45,583 --> 00:02:48,250
This is the third time in two weeks.

32
00:02:48,333 --> 00:02:50,458
Do you still want to work here?

33
00:02:51,333 --> 00:02:53,416
If you can,
get someone to take your shift.

34
00:02:53,500 --> 00:02:55,958
But you can't,
so your coworkers have to cover for you.

35
00:02:56,041 --> 00:02:57,416
How is this okay?

36
00:02:57,500 --> 00:02:58,708
Sir, I'm really sorry.

37
00:02:58,791 --> 00:03:00,791
I feel bad for Nini too. I have no excuse.

38
00:03:00,875 --> 00:03:04,166
Something came up
unexpectedly today, so I--

39
00:03:04,250 --> 00:03:07,833
Hold on.
You also said that the last two times.

40
00:03:07,916 --> 00:03:10,916
I really don't know… I don't know
if I should let you keep this job.

41
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:13,541
Sir, please.
Give me another chance. I'll work hard.

42
00:03:13,625 --> 00:03:16,250
Because my dad had to
go to the hospital today and…

43
00:03:16,333 --> 00:03:19,125
Something came up,
but I've asked a caregiver for help.

44
00:03:19,208 --> 00:03:21,500
So please give me another chance. I will…

45
00:03:21,583 --> 00:03:23,291
I really need this job. I--

46
00:03:23,375 --> 00:03:24,625
Jeez,

47
00:03:24,708 --> 00:03:28,041
why do I have to deal with
your personal issues?

48
00:03:35,166 --> 00:03:37,416
Do I have to tell you what to do next?

49
00:03:43,541 --> 00:03:44,458
Thank you, sir.

50
00:03:46,208 --> 00:03:47,166
Sir, I'm off now.

51
00:03:47,250 --> 00:03:48,083
Bye.

52
00:03:49,458 --> 00:03:51,750
- Remember to pay me double for my hours.
- Okay.

53
00:03:54,375 --> 00:03:56,458
- Hello.
- Good morning. Thank you.

54
00:04:12,625 --> 00:04:14,250
<i>I'm not a mom to any child,</i>

55
00:04:16,041 --> 00:04:19,583
<i>but I've ended up mothering my dad.</i>

56
00:04:39,875 --> 00:04:40,875
Here.

57
00:04:41,708 --> 00:04:43,541
Fine. You're not eating?

58
00:04:43,625 --> 00:04:46,125
If you don't eat,
thunder and lightning will strike.

59
00:04:47,875 --> 00:04:52,708
WEDNESDAY, ORDER DIAPERS AND PADS ONLINE
5:00 P.M. NIGHT SHIFT

60
00:04:59,500 --> 00:05:02,416
Hello? I'm the family of room 223. Yes.

61
00:05:02,500 --> 00:05:04,333
You're a ghost.

62
00:05:04,416 --> 00:05:06,875
Keep it down. I'm on the phone.

63
00:05:06,958 --> 00:05:09,291
- No. Rock, paper…
- Rock…

64
00:05:09,375 --> 00:05:10,250
I'm sorry.

65
00:05:10,333 --> 00:05:14,166
Yes, I'd like to ask if my parents

66
00:05:14,250 --> 00:05:16,541
are doing well lately.

67
00:05:18,958 --> 00:05:20,333
I understand.

68
00:05:20,416 --> 00:05:23,625
It must have been too dry.
Their skin itched, so they scratched it.

69
00:05:23,708 --> 00:05:25,000
Yes, you guys are great.

70
00:05:25,083 --> 00:05:27,875
You're attentive and professional.
I'm really grateful.

71
00:05:27,958 --> 00:05:29,875
<i>Please take good care of them.</i>

72
00:05:30,916 --> 00:05:33,875
<i>Okay. I'll try to visit them soon.</i>

73
00:05:33,958 --> 00:05:36,208
<i>Probably next month, yeah.</i>

74
00:05:42,875 --> 00:05:43,708
Here.

75
00:05:46,708 --> 00:05:48,083
You don't want water?

76
00:05:48,166 --> 00:05:50,416
You've been drinking
very little water lately.

77
00:05:52,083 --> 00:05:53,750
Your lips are chapped.

78
00:05:57,333 --> 00:05:58,916
I can't see things up close now.

79
00:06:00,458 --> 00:06:02,416
Let me moisten your lips.

80
00:06:04,041 --> 00:06:08,583
I received the insurance policy slip
that you bought over 40 years ago.

81
00:06:08,666 --> 00:06:10,875
Looks like you cashed out most of it,

82
00:06:11,375 --> 00:06:13,000
so there's not much left.

83
00:06:13,083 --> 00:06:15,875
They wanted me to deal with it, but

84
00:06:16,833 --> 00:06:18,666
they need your signature.

85
00:06:19,875 --> 00:06:21,291
Don't blame me for this.

86
00:06:22,833 --> 00:06:24,041
I signed it for you.

87
00:06:26,791 --> 00:06:29,666
You know,
I'm good at copying your signature.

88
00:06:30,166 --> 00:06:32,875
My teachers never noticed
that I copied your signature.

89
00:06:37,416 --> 00:06:41,125
By the way, Chang Kai asked
if I'd go to Singapore with him.

90
00:06:41,208 --> 00:06:42,708
Do I want to go with him?

91
00:06:42,791 --> 00:06:45,083
I'm telling you, of course, I do.

92
00:06:45,916 --> 00:06:47,291
But I can't.

93
00:06:49,291 --> 00:06:51,750
I know you'd tell me

94
00:06:52,750 --> 00:06:54,875
not to worry about you and just go.

95
00:06:54,958 --> 00:06:55,833
Right?

96
00:06:59,583 --> 00:07:01,500
Well, I'll admit, I did consider

97
00:07:02,291 --> 00:07:03,541
leaving you behind.

98
00:07:13,791 --> 00:07:14,791
Sometimes,

99
00:07:15,500 --> 00:07:19,583
I don't know if I'm taking care of you
out of responsibility or guilt.

100
00:07:25,875 --> 00:07:26,791
I'm actually…

101
00:07:33,750 --> 00:07:35,125
I'm actually exhausted.

102
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:40,000
But I feel so bad for you.

103
00:07:59,291 --> 00:08:00,583
You know what?

104
00:08:00,666 --> 00:08:01,625
Sometimes,

105
00:08:03,041 --> 00:08:05,916
I feel like you're a handful of sand.
It's as if…

106
00:08:07,375 --> 00:08:09,250
It's as if I can hold you in my hand,

107
00:08:09,333 --> 00:08:13,875
but if I loosen my grip,
you'll slip right through my fingers.

108
00:08:15,291 --> 00:08:17,208
Do you get what I mean?

109
00:08:20,208 --> 00:08:22,625
You know I hate it when you call my name.

110
00:08:25,208 --> 00:08:27,791
But it's been a while.
Can you call my name?

111
00:08:29,958 --> 00:08:30,875
Cheng Le-le.

112
00:08:34,291 --> 00:08:35,291
Cheng Le-le.

113
00:08:49,541 --> 00:08:51,666
Dad, I'm sorry. I'm not whining but…

114
00:08:54,416 --> 00:08:56,125
I'm just a bit tired.

115
00:08:57,416 --> 00:08:59,791
I'm repeating the same chores every day.

116
00:09:03,416 --> 00:09:05,875
Can you tell me if you'll get better?

117
00:09:05,958 --> 00:09:08,500
Will everything get better?

118
00:09:12,208 --> 00:09:13,583
Frankly, I'm terrified.

119
00:09:14,333 --> 00:09:16,166
I'm afraid you'll pass away suddenly.

120
00:09:16,250 --> 00:09:17,833
But what frightens me more

121
00:09:17,916 --> 00:09:19,583
is you hanging on like this.

122
00:09:24,833 --> 00:09:26,958
I'm a bad daughter. I'm sorry.

123
00:09:27,041 --> 00:09:28,666
Hit me…

124
00:09:33,750 --> 00:09:34,583
Just hit me.

125
00:10:24,083 --> 00:10:26,500
Yes. Ms. Huang is on leave today.

126
00:10:26,583 --> 00:10:28,583
I'll check her desk for the info.

127
00:10:28,666 --> 00:10:30,833
Sure. I'll call you back. Bye.

128
00:10:30,916 --> 00:10:31,916
Where's Su-fei?

129
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:34,000
She takes this day off every year.

130
00:10:35,125 --> 00:10:37,541
The pitch is next week. Are you all done?

131
00:10:38,125 --> 00:10:41,250
Yes, we've planned
a cosmetic surgery package for besties.

132
00:10:41,333 --> 00:10:43,833
And we've contacted a few beauty clinics.

133
00:10:43,916 --> 00:10:46,083
I'll finish up
this weekend and report to you.

134
00:10:46,166 --> 00:10:47,958
Taking time off before the work's done?

135
00:10:48,041 --> 00:10:49,708
I've had enough of veterans.

136
00:10:51,375 --> 00:10:52,250
Hello?

137
00:10:52,333 --> 00:10:55,125
Ms. Chen. Yes, she did.

138
00:10:55,625 --> 00:10:57,583
Okay, I'll send it to you later.

139
00:10:57,666 --> 00:10:58,583
Okay, no problem.

140
00:10:58,666 --> 00:11:02,583
FAMILY DAY

141
00:11:06,791 --> 00:11:08,833
I know you don't like sweets.

142
00:11:08,916 --> 00:11:11,458
But this is the Hokkaido cream roll cake.

143
00:11:11,541 --> 00:11:13,250
It's worth a try.

144
00:11:14,208 --> 00:11:15,833
Strawberries from Hokkaido.

145
00:11:17,250 --> 00:11:19,541
It feels ceremonial, right?

146
00:11:20,708 --> 00:11:23,041
Everyone's into camping these days.

147
00:11:28,083 --> 00:11:33,416
IN MEMORY OF
HUANG WEI-CHENG, CHUNG HSIN-HUEI

148
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:36,916
Dad, Mom,

149
00:11:37,708 --> 00:11:38,625
how are you?

150
00:11:41,583 --> 00:11:42,833
I'm okay.

151
00:11:44,166 --> 00:11:45,708
I'm just a bit tired.

152
00:11:46,416 --> 00:11:48,791
I spent New Year's
in Hokkaido again this year.

153
00:11:49,583 --> 00:11:50,416
Of course,

154
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:52,708
I had New Year's Eve dinner alone.

155
00:11:54,375 --> 00:11:56,666
Guess what my favorite moment was?

156
00:11:56,750 --> 00:11:59,750
When I sent the tourists
into the restaurant for dinner.

157
00:11:59,833 --> 00:12:01,750
Wow, in that split second…

158
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:06,000
everything went quiet.

159
00:12:08,458 --> 00:12:11,208
I could almost hear
the snow falling on the ground.

160
00:12:17,666 --> 00:12:19,500
They found me pitiful,

161
00:12:20,208 --> 00:12:22,083
but I felt carefree.

162
00:12:22,708 --> 00:12:23,666
There's no need…

163
00:12:25,250 --> 00:12:28,041
No need
for New Year greetings and small talk,

164
00:12:28,958 --> 00:12:32,250
like wishing everyone good wealth.

165
00:12:40,583 --> 00:12:42,916
I still haven't told Le-le and Chia-yun

166
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:45,333
that you passed away in a car accident.

167
00:12:46,083 --> 00:12:49,791
I know it's not right of me
to keep such a secret from my besties.

168
00:12:51,541 --> 00:12:53,500
But I don't want them to pity me.

169
00:12:56,666 --> 00:12:58,541
I'm afraid to be consoled.

170
00:13:01,125 --> 00:13:03,333
I know what they'd say to me.

171
00:13:16,375 --> 00:13:18,791
Lies are sometimes just like wishes.

172
00:13:21,541 --> 00:13:24,583
The longer you've lied,
the more you buy into them.

173
00:13:25,583 --> 00:13:27,250
I believe you're still alive

174
00:13:28,833 --> 00:13:30,791
and you're just living elsewhere.

175
00:13:35,250 --> 00:13:36,166
Dad, Mom.

176
00:13:39,291 --> 00:13:41,041
I miss you so much.

177
00:13:43,125 --> 00:13:46,041
But I can't seem to remember
what you looked like.

178
00:13:53,041 --> 00:13:54,750
I'll do my best to remember.

179
00:14:12,916 --> 00:14:14,125
You're home from work?

180
00:14:14,208 --> 00:14:15,041
Dad.

181
00:14:16,833 --> 00:14:18,875
How did you get back on your feet?

182
00:14:19,583 --> 00:14:22,208
Take your jacket off.
We're having noodles soon.

183
00:14:27,166 --> 00:14:28,708
Hurry and go wash up.

184
00:14:28,791 --> 00:14:30,291
Then come out for dinner.

185
00:14:30,375 --> 00:14:31,500
Go and wash up now.

186
00:14:53,916 --> 00:14:54,833
Dad.

187
00:15:00,083 --> 00:15:01,166
Dad.

188
00:15:01,875 --> 00:15:02,708
Dad.

189
00:15:33,166 --> 00:15:37,375
I'M CHENG KUANG-CHI. I'M 77.
MY DAUGHTER IS CHENG LE-LE.

190
00:15:41,041 --> 00:15:43,708
<i>Mr. Cheng keeps getting hospitalized</i>

191
00:15:43,791 --> 00:15:46,666
<i>because of pneumonia from choking.</i>

192
00:15:46,750 --> 00:15:50,208
<i>Each time there's inflammation,</i>
<i>it could lead to other complications.</i>

193
00:15:50,291 --> 00:15:53,000
<i>We suggest</i>
<i>placing a nasal feeding tube for now.</i>

194
00:15:53,083 --> 00:15:55,125
<i>But he said</i>
<i>he doesn't want to be intubated.</i>

195
00:15:55,208 --> 00:15:58,291
<i>A nasal feeding tube isn't intubation.</i>
<i>It gives him enough nutrition.</i>

196
00:15:58,375 --> 00:16:02,125
<i>It also prevents him from choking</i>
<i>and suffocating or going into shock again.</i>

197
00:16:39,916 --> 00:16:41,500
Dad, I'm sorry.

198
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,000
<i>Do it this way.</i>

199
00:16:51,083 --> 00:16:53,000
- Release it faster, it drips faster.
- Okay.

200
00:16:53,083 --> 00:16:57,291
So we tie it like this
to slow down the flow.

201
00:16:57,375 --> 00:17:00,250
Otherwise, it'd fill with air
and his stomach would feel very bloated.

202
00:17:09,458 --> 00:17:11,458
<i>One, two, three.</i>

203
00:17:11,541 --> 00:17:13,250
- Nod.
- Nod.

204
00:17:13,750 --> 00:17:15,583
Here, try harder.

205
00:17:15,666 --> 00:17:16,541
Good job, Dad.

206
00:17:16,625 --> 00:17:18,958
Okay. Hold it up.

207
00:17:19,041 --> 00:17:20,708
Good.

208
00:17:21,666 --> 00:17:22,916
Mr. Cheng.

209
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:24,375
- Cheng Kuang-chi.
- Okay.

210
00:17:25,125 --> 00:17:26,791
- Sorry.
- How about we get the pillow?

211
00:17:26,875 --> 00:17:28,000
- Okay.
- Here, I got you.

212
00:17:28,083 --> 00:17:29,458
- I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

213
00:20:38,375 --> 00:20:40,416
It feels better to be home, right?

214
00:20:49,958 --> 00:20:50,958
<i>Cheng Kuang-chi.</i>

215
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:54,333
Cheng Kuang-chi.

216
00:20:54,416 --> 00:20:57,375
I'm your daughter, Cheng Le-le.

217
00:21:00,041 --> 00:21:03,666
I'm your daughter, Cheng Le-le.

218
00:21:08,666 --> 00:21:10,791
You took this in Spain.

219
00:21:10,875 --> 00:21:13,583
And you brought me…

220
00:21:13,666 --> 00:21:17,708
I think it was a teddy bear?
I still have it.

221
00:21:21,333 --> 00:21:22,583
You were in the States.

222
00:21:26,916 --> 00:21:30,541
I've always liked this photo.

223
00:21:30,625 --> 00:21:32,833
You were good-looking as a young man.

224
00:21:34,291 --> 00:21:38,250
I remember how my classmates
used to say, "Your dad is so handsome!"

225
00:21:39,416 --> 00:21:41,541
But I think you aged like fine wine.

226
00:21:43,541 --> 00:21:45,791
Look, our family photo.

227
00:21:45,875 --> 00:21:49,166
Who is this kid?

228
00:21:49,750 --> 00:21:50,791
Cheng Le-le.

229
00:21:51,958 --> 00:21:53,333
Who is Cheng Le-le?

230
00:21:53,958 --> 00:21:55,458
Me.

231
00:21:55,541 --> 00:21:59,166
See? Told you it was blue.

232
00:21:59,791 --> 00:22:02,250
The first bike you got me.

233
00:22:28,875 --> 00:22:31,833
LE-LE'S FIRST SUMMER BREAK
AFTER ELEMENTARY SCHOOL

234
00:22:31,916 --> 00:22:33,916
<i>Can you not send me away?</i>

235
00:22:35,208 --> 00:22:36,958
I'm not sending you away.

236
00:22:37,458 --> 00:22:40,291
I'm just worried
no one's looking after you.

237
00:22:44,291 --> 00:22:46,833
Hey, it's going to rain soon.
Let's go home.

238
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:51,333
Did she tell you

239
00:22:52,875 --> 00:22:54,541
why she left us?

240
00:23:01,500 --> 00:23:02,750
<i>- Dad, don't let go.</i>
<i>- Okay.</i>

241
00:23:02,833 --> 00:23:05,583
- Dad, please don't let go.
- Wait.

242
00:25:29,666 --> 00:25:30,500
Hello?

243
00:25:30,583 --> 00:25:33,458
<i>I couldn't reach you these days.</i>
<i>Is everything okay?</i>

244
00:25:33,958 --> 00:25:34,875
<i>How's your dad?</i>

245
00:25:35,750 --> 00:25:36,666
<i>Is he okay?</i>

246
00:25:39,875 --> 00:25:40,708
He's gone.

247
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:42,958
<i>Where did he go?</i>

248
00:25:46,375 --> 00:25:47,583
<i>Where are you?</i>

249
00:25:47,666 --> 00:25:48,750
<i>I'll come see you.</i>

250
00:25:49,250 --> 00:25:50,333
You don't have to.

251
00:25:51,625 --> 00:25:52,500
I'm okay.

252
00:25:54,541 --> 00:25:57,458
I got to spend
the last two days with him quietly.

253
00:25:58,291 --> 00:25:59,833
I think it was quite nice.

254
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:05,833
This is bound to happen, right?

255
00:26:08,958 --> 00:26:09,833
Don't worry.

256
00:26:10,625 --> 00:26:11,750
That's all for now.

257
00:26:36,458 --> 00:26:39,041
Ma'am, here's
the death certificate you requested.

